Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

01:28.134 --> 01:29.398
Rochelle: James.

01:29.400 --> 01:31.932
♪♪

01:31.934 --> 01:32.932
James.

01:32.934 --> 01:36.598
♪♪

01:39.667 --> 01:42.932
♪♪

01:42.934 --> 01:44.199
Rochelle.

01:49.267 --> 01:50.465
I needed that.

01:50.467 --> 01:52.398
Oh, yes, you did.

01:52.400 --> 01:55.032
You've had a stressful day,
and it's not even noon.

01:59.400 --> 02:01.065
You didn't order room service.

02:01.067 --> 02:03.132
No, I mean...

02:03.134 --> 02:05.732
Folks might get the wrong idea.

02:12.634 --> 02:15.399
Listen, I want to thank you...

02:17.801 --> 02:19.998
for listening earlier.

02:20.000 --> 02:21.998
My pleasure.

02:22.000 --> 02:24.532
I just wish I could've
done more to comfort you.

02:27.367 --> 02:28.765
I still can.

02:30.967 --> 02:32.399
I'm still married.

02:36.467 --> 02:38.599
So, where are you
off to from here?

02:39.600 --> 02:40.600
Calvary.

02:42.334 --> 02:44.099
You can't take one day off?

02:45.734 --> 02:47.332
I tried that once

02:47.334 --> 02:51.065
and, uh... Didn't know
what to do with myself.

02:51.067 --> 02:52.598
Let me help you
with this collar.

02:52.600 --> 02:54.332
Oh, I got it.

02:54.334 --> 02:57.398
Wow, I love this cross.

02:57.400 --> 02:59.131
♪♪

02:59.133 --> 03:02.299
It's so... Beautiful.

03:04.600 --> 03:05.999
I'm still married.

03:07.467 --> 03:09.399
But she threw you out.

03:10.467 --> 03:13.965
I'm married to god's vision
of the man I'm meant to be.

03:16.934 --> 03:18.132
Well... mae...

03:20.400 --> 03:22.665
whatever she does
is beside the point.

03:22.667 --> 03:25.632
♪♪

03:34.434 --> 03:36.565
Oh, lord Jesus.

03:36.567 --> 03:37.965
What?

03:37.967 --> 03:39.498
It's my granddaughter.

03:39.500 --> 03:41.298
♪♪

03:41.300 --> 03:43.865
It seems zora's run off
with that boy.

03:43.867 --> 03:47.499
♪♪

04:10.934 --> 04:14.532
♪♪

04:14.534 --> 04:16.732
I didn't know what else to do.

04:16.733 --> 04:19.197
Isaiah hit her so hard.

04:19.200 --> 04:20.732
Grace: Sophia,
you did the right thing.

04:20.733 --> 04:23.732
I know, but maybe if
I didn't tell him,

04:23.734 --> 04:25.899
zora wouldn't have run away.

04:25.901 --> 04:27.631
Is there any news?

04:27.633 --> 04:30.165
Hey, hey.

04:30.167 --> 04:32.032
Not yet, unfortunately.

04:32.034 --> 04:34.098
Okay.

04:34.100 --> 04:35.765
I'm so worried about zora.

04:35.767 --> 04:37.298
I've just been
prayin' the whole way.

04:37.300 --> 04:40.565
I was prayin'
and cryin' and prayin'.

04:40.567 --> 04:42.065
Where were you coming from?

04:43.600 --> 04:46.332
Nashville, my first show.

04:47.201 --> 04:50.098
But now I got to stay a few days
and handle things with Kevin.

04:50.100 --> 04:51.365
Kevin's back?

04:51.367 --> 04:52.232
Mm-hmm.
God help me.

04:52.234 --> 04:54.165
And making noises about custody.

04:54.167 --> 04:56.332
After he walked out
and vanished?

04:56.334 --> 04:58.665
Apparently,
but he only spoke to mama.

04:58.667 --> 05:00.532
Well, I wouldn't
call it speaking.

05:00.534 --> 05:01.865
He showed up and crowed

05:01.867 --> 05:03.932
he'd got some legal advice
from Aaron,

05:03.934 --> 05:06.465
or it seemed like that anyway
from his tone.

05:06.467 --> 05:08.199
I'm sorry you have to
deal with that.

05:08.201 --> 05:10.731
No, it's... it's fine.

05:10.733 --> 05:12.465
My next show's in Jackson
Monday,

05:12.467 --> 05:15.598
so Jabari's coming to pick me up
tomorrow after church.

05:15.600 --> 05:17.598
Sophia, sweetheart,
can you help me

05:17.600 --> 05:19.198
get the rest of
my stuff upstairs?

05:19.200 --> 05:21.598
Yeah, I'll grab some bags
and take them up.

05:22.167 --> 05:23.399
Thank you, baby.

05:27.800 --> 05:30.065
Where's daddy?
Is he at Jacob's?

05:30.067 --> 05:31.067
No.

05:34.133 --> 05:35.865
We called him.
He knows.

05:35.867 --> 05:37.699
He's on his way
to the church right now.

05:38.701 --> 05:41.365
Wow.

05:41.367 --> 05:45.098
I've been gone for a day
and all of this happens?

05:45.100 --> 05:47.065
Y'all need me here
more than you think.

05:54.667 --> 05:56.332
How you holdin' up, mama?

05:58.333 --> 06:00.499
Don't give me that sympathy.

06:01.934 --> 06:03.165
Excuse me?

06:04.900 --> 06:07.132
When you came home
for faith's funeral...

06:08.267 --> 06:10.998
you promised me that
you hadn't come to sow discord.

06:11.000 --> 06:13.532
Now look at us.
Look at me.

06:13.534 --> 06:14.932
I came back to deal with Mac.

06:14.934 --> 06:16.798
Oh, and we're all still
paying for that, grace.

06:16.800 --> 06:19.265
Oh.

06:19.267 --> 06:20.465
I know you're upset...

06:20.467 --> 06:22.798
You and my sister...
You're never happy

06:22.800 --> 06:26.665
until everybody is stewin'
in their own shame and sin.

06:26.667 --> 06:29.498
Grace... you don't know
the meaning of that word.

06:29.500 --> 06:30.732
Now I'm a little confused.

06:30.734 --> 06:32.198
Oh, a little confused?

06:32.200 --> 06:34.065
I didn't make zora run away,

06:34.067 --> 06:35.598
I didn't make Kevin gay,

06:35.600 --> 06:37.332
and I certainly didn't send
daddy out the door to auntie.

06:37.334 --> 06:39.332
Now what did I do, mom?!

06:39.334 --> 06:42.298
Bang around this family
like a bull in a China shop

06:42.300 --> 06:45.165
until everything's broken,
actin' like it's god's work.

06:45.167 --> 06:46.898
In this family, it is!

06:46.900 --> 06:50.465
Don't you say
anything like that to me!

06:50.467 --> 06:53.332
♪♪

