♪ yeah ♪

08:09.042 --> 08:11.042
𝒯𝓇𝒶𝓃𝓈𝓁𝒶𝓉e 𝓊𝓃𝒾𝒸𝒶𝓉 E𝒩𝒢LI𝒮H

08:11.067 --> 08:12.631
Where you think you're going?

08:12.633 --> 08:14.899
To my room.
Mnh-mnh. Give me that bag.

08:14.901 --> 08:16.031
Why?

08:16.033 --> 08:18.965
Give me the bag.

08:18.967 --> 08:20.365
Give me the bag.

08:20.367 --> 08:22.298
I want the wallet, atm card,

08:22.300 --> 08:23.565
which you can forget about.

08:23.567 --> 08:25.732
Everything.
You're on lockdown.

08:25.734 --> 08:27.898
Phone, too.
I know you got a new one.

08:27.900 --> 08:29.999
I need my phone.
What if there's an emergency?

08:30.001 --> 08:31.732
This <i> is</i> an emergency.

08:31.734 --> 08:33.265
From now on, your mother and I

08:33.267 --> 08:34.732
will be clocking you
every step of the way.

08:34.734 --> 08:38.131
We will have eyes on you 24-7.

08:38.134 --> 08:39.265
So don't worry.

08:39.267 --> 08:40.965
Something happens, we'll see it.

08:44.734 --> 08:46.731
You want something to eat?

08:46.733 --> 08:49.132
Oh.
I'm allowed to eat?

08:49.134 --> 08:50.665
Is it mealtime in the prison?

08:50.667 --> 08:54.398
Hey, that tone... use it again.
Jacob.

08:54.400 --> 08:55.732
We found this girl

08:55.734 --> 08:59.132
10 miles shy of the state line
in a roach motel

08:59.134 --> 09:00.798
and you're talking to me
like <i> I'm</i> the problem?

09:00.800 --> 09:03.665
Okay, we're all tired.
Let's just take a beat.

09:05.034 --> 09:07.532
You better be glad we didn't
press charges against that boy.

09:07.534 --> 09:09.665
You should be glad he didn't
press charges against <i> you.</i>

09:09.667 --> 09:12.465
Don't act like you didn't
cut some sort of deal.

09:12.467 --> 09:15.499
Little girl,
anything in your pockets?

09:15.501 --> 09:17.998
Want to check?
Yes, I do.

09:18.000 --> 09:19.232
Want to act like
a little criminal,

09:19.234 --> 09:20.732
then I'm gonna
treat you like one.

09:20.734 --> 09:22.565
All right, <i>now</i> you can go.

09:22.567 --> 09:23.665
Go to your room.

09:26.467 --> 09:28.132
Don't behave like your sister,
you hear me?

09:28.134 --> 09:30.065
Yes, sir.

09:31.033 --> 09:32.965
Now what?

09:32.967 --> 09:34.698
Hello?

09:34.700 --> 09:37.599
Yes, gigi.
Yes, she's home.

09:37.601 --> 09:39.799
Yes, can you let everybody know
that she's home?

09:39.801 --> 09:42.298
Okay, thank you.

09:44.134 --> 09:46.165
You're grounded for life!

09:46.167 --> 09:48.665
And don't slam my door.

09:48.667 --> 09:52.465
I'll take it off the hinges!

09:57.000 --> 09:59.899
♪♪

10:04.933 --> 10:06.065
Hello.

10:06.067 --> 10:07.265
Excuse me.

10:07.267 --> 10:08.598
♪♪

10:08.600 --> 10:09.965
I'm... I'm sorry?

10:09.967 --> 10:12.498
You'd like to see the bishop?

10:12.500 --> 10:14.232
Yes, if he's available.

10:14.234 --> 10:16.865
My guess is he's not.

10:16.867 --> 10:17.899
Oh.

10:21.567 --> 10:23.365
Miss cross is here to see you.

10:23.367 --> 10:26.432
James:
<i>Oh, you send her right in.</i>

10:26.434 --> 10:28.032
Well, look at me.

10:28.034 --> 10:30.465
Just like Moses
partin' seas left and right.

10:30.467 --> 10:32.465
Oh, you can
leave that right there.

10:32.467 --> 10:34.065
Oh, I'll take it off your hands.

10:43.734 --> 10:44.765
Hey.

10:46.067 --> 10:47.798
Hey.

10:47.800 --> 10:49.398
I've been praying for zora.

10:49.400 --> 10:51.265
She's home safe, praise god.

10:51.267 --> 10:53.065
Oh, praise god.

10:53.067 --> 10:54.465
I-I know it's crazy,

10:54.467 --> 10:57.132
but I feel like that little girl
is a part of my family.

10:58.367 --> 11:00.032
Would you mind
closing that door, please?

11:00.034 --> 11:01.132
Oh, of course, yes.

11:13.433 --> 11:16.831
So, how are you holdin' up?

11:16.833 --> 11:20.298
Listen...

11:20.300 --> 11:22.298
About what happened today...

11:22.300 --> 11:24.865
I know, I-I was wrong.

11:24.867 --> 11:25.867
No, no, no, no.

11:27.000 --> 11:28.732
<i>I</i> was wrong.

11:28.734 --> 11:30.465
It was all me.

11:30.467 --> 11:31.999
Well, you <i> are</i> still married.

11:33.200 --> 11:34.332
I am.

11:37.234 --> 11:41.731
Uh, our doors are always open
for you to come and worship...

11:41.733 --> 11:45.332
But I don't think that we should

11:45.334 --> 11:47.165
be spending
personal time together.

11:49.134 --> 11:50.832
Got it.

11:52.134 --> 11:54.465
Bishop, you're a dear man,

11:54.467 --> 11:58.565
and I would give you
anything you needed...

11:59.667 --> 12:01.732
including space.

12:06.167 --> 12:08.498
Hey, Corinne,
is the bishop busy?

12:08.500 --> 12:10.532
No, go right on in.

12:16.800 --> 12:17.932
Uh, gigi.

12:17.934 --> 12:21.465
Hi. I, um, I was actually
on my way out.

12:21.467 --> 12:22.531
Yes, yeah.

12:22.533 --> 12:23.665
I'll see you tomorrow morning?

12:23.667 --> 12:25.398
Yeah, i-in church.

12:25.400 --> 12:26.699
Yes, yes.

12:28.800 --> 12:31.899
♪♪

12:35.900 --> 12:38.532
Buy you a cup of coffee?

12:38.534 --> 12:39.998
Please.

12:40.000 --> 12:42.899
♪♪

12:48.267 --> 12:49.899
Kerissa:
How ya feeling?

12:52.134 --> 12:55.932
Honey, I know things
are a little tense right now

12:55.934 --> 12:58.732
and it's gonna take
some adjusting to...

13:00.867 --> 13:02.265
but I want you to know

13:02.267 --> 13:04.465
that your father and I
only want the best for you.

13:06.734 --> 13:09.432
We love you very much.

13:11.534 --> 13:12.865
Do you know that?

13:23.834 --> 13:26.431
I'm sorry I ran away.

13:26.433 --> 13:28.565
I just...

13:28.567 --> 13:30.765
I didn't know what to do.

13:30.767 --> 13:32.232
Everyone saw,

13:32.234 --> 13:35.232
and I-I couldn't just stay here
after I ruined everything.

13:36.700 --> 13:41.732
Oh, honey.

13:41.734 --> 13:43.765
You didn't ruin <i> anything.</i>

13:49.334 --> 13:51.965
Dad could've gone
to jail or something.

13:54.534 --> 13:57.132
I just wish
he wasn't so mad at me.

13:59.867 --> 14:01.732
Come here, come on.

14:01.734 --> 14:03.932
Come on, it's okay.

14:03.934 --> 14:06.065
I don't know what else to do.

14:06.067 --> 14:08.132
It's all right, baby.

14:09.134 --> 14:11.998
It's gonna be okay.
It's okay.

14:12.000 --> 14:13.665
♪♪

14:13.667 --> 14:16.098
James: How are you doing,
gigi?

14:16.100 --> 14:18.598
Grace: I was gonna ask you
that same thing, daddy.

14:18.600 --> 14:21.399
Well, listen, I'm fantastic.

14:21.401 --> 14:23.165
Really?

14:23.167 --> 14:25.832
Yeah.
Come on.

14:25.834 --> 14:28.098
I am out of
the shadow of a mad woman

14:28.100 --> 14:29.365
who would believe lies about me

14:29.367 --> 14:30.865
told by her worst enemy.

14:30.867 --> 14:32.731
Is that what they are?

14:32.733 --> 14:34.065
What do you mean?

14:34.067 --> 14:37.132
Are they lies?
Aunt mavis is lying?

14:37.134 --> 14:38.399
Look, that's none
of your business.

14:38.401 --> 14:40.932
♪♪

14:40.934 --> 14:42.665
So mavis isn't lying.

14:42.667 --> 14:44.732
Stay out of it.

14:44.734 --> 14:48.732
It's better for everyone,
trust me.

14:48.734 --> 14:51.665
♪♪

14:54.300 --> 14:56.032
The spending has to end.

14:56.034 --> 14:57.965
The homeless aren't
giving any money.

14:57.967 --> 15:00.065
Britney,
the budget meeting's over.

15:00.067 --> 15:01.631
But the money problems aren't.

15:01.633 --> 15:03.331
Look, I know you're just
trying to do your job,

15:03.333 --> 15:04.531
but I can't do this right now.

15:04.533 --> 15:06.865
You do understand
that ever since you took over,

15:06.867 --> 15:08.398
money's been
going through this church

15:08.400 --> 15:10.332
faster than green grass
through a goose.

15:10.334 --> 15:13.332
Britney, the board passed
a unanimous resolution

15:13.334 --> 15:15.432
to partner with real church...
Unanimous.

15:15.434 --> 15:17.365
Because they didn't know
how much it would cost.

15:17.367 --> 15:20.998
Look, we're gonna start
streaming live next month.

15:21.000 --> 15:23.232
There'll be plenty of money.

15:23.234 --> 15:25.132
Now, this meeting's over.

15:25.134 --> 15:27.265
You are gonna
bankrupt this church.

15:27.267 --> 15:28.798
Thank you for your concern.

15:28.800 --> 15:31.232
♪♪

15:39.334 --> 15:40.332
Hey.

15:40.334 --> 15:41.334
Hey.

15:42.800 --> 15:45.865
You know I've never heard her
speak to basie like that.

15:45.867 --> 15:48.398
If it was up to me,
I'd fire her.

15:48.400 --> 15:51.398
♪♪

15:51.400 --> 15:52.432
Just sayin'.

15:52.434 --> 15:58.131
♪♪

15:58.133 --> 15:59.799
Kevin: He's my son.
I want to see him, charity.

15:59.801 --> 16:01.265
Charity: Well, maybe you
should've thought about that

16:01.267 --> 16:02.732
before you full-on
ghosted on us.

16:02.734 --> 16:04.198
I wasn't thinking when I left.

16:04.200 --> 16:06.465
Kevin, fatherhood is not some...

16:06.467 --> 16:09.332
Club you just drop in on
when you feel like it.

16:09.334 --> 16:11.865
I know.
I regret what I did.

16:11.867 --> 16:13.598
I just had to
get right with myself,

16:13.600 --> 16:14.931
and I'm ready
to be a father now.

16:14.933 --> 16:16.799
I don't know
that I'm ready to let you.

16:16.801 --> 16:18.732
Now, I'm gonna tell you
what I told your mother...

16:18.734 --> 16:20.198
I'm ready to go to court.

16:20.200 --> 16:23.932
Kevin, I am in the middle
of a tour right now.

16:23.934 --> 16:25.799
Then just leave him
with me, then.

16:27.067 --> 16:30.398
I... No.

16:30.400 --> 16:33.932
How do I know you won't get in
some strange mood again?

16:33.934 --> 16:37.265
How do I know that you won't
write another note

16:37.267 --> 16:38.398
and disappear?

16:38.400 --> 16:40.132
Absolutely not.

16:40.134 --> 16:42.332
Charity, I have a right
to see my son.

16:42.334 --> 16:44.532
Charity!
Oh, god.

16:49.734 --> 16:52.799
♪♪

16:56.334 --> 16:57.798
Good morning.

16:57.800 --> 17:00.165
♪♪

17:00.167 --> 17:01.632
Chai latte.

17:01.634 --> 17:03.165
Oh, you're so thoughtful.

17:04.800 --> 17:05.998
What's that?

17:06.000 --> 17:07.999
It came earlier this morning.

17:21.532 --> 17:22.799
Mae: Well,
it's good to see

17:22.800 --> 17:24.598
your sense of entitlement
hasn't suffered

17:24.599 --> 17:25.732
since you cheated your way

17:25.733 --> 17:27.765
out of every good thing
that god ever gave you.

17:29.000 --> 17:31.132
Mae, we have a problem.

17:31.134 --> 17:32.665
Where were you this morning

17:32.667 --> 17:34.198
when your granddaughter
was missing, James?

17:34.200 --> 17:35.298
My phone was off.

17:35.300 --> 17:37.565
Answer the question, James.
Where were you?

17:37.567 --> 17:39.898
The biltmore, sleeping...

17:39.900 --> 17:42.865
Since I was ejected
from my home by a mad woman.

17:44.067 --> 17:46.865
Look, do you want
to hear about this or not?

17:46.867 --> 17:48.732
What is that?

17:48.734 --> 17:51.331
It's a letter
from the I.R.S.

17:51.333 --> 17:52.531
The what?
Read it if you want,

17:52.533 --> 17:54.199
but I'll give you
the <i> reader's digest</i> version.

17:54.201 --> 17:57.198
When Mac said he would take care
of our problems with the I.R.S.,

17:57.200 --> 17:59.532
what he did was
pay some joker a bribe.

17:59.534 --> 18:01.665
Now that joker's been caught.

18:01.667 --> 18:02.865
The bottom line...

18:04.800 --> 18:08.532
if we don't pay the I.R.S.
$2 million in the next 90 days,

18:08.534 --> 18:10.499
they're gonna come after us
for tax evasion.

18:10.501 --> 18:12.332
How could you let this happen?!

18:12.334 --> 18:13.765
It was your brother, Mae!

18:13.767 --> 18:15.765
How are we supposed to pay that,
James?

18:15.767 --> 18:18.665
I don't know.
I don't know.

18:18.667 --> 18:20.232
But what I do know is this...

18:20.234 --> 18:22.298
Whether we take
a special offering,

18:22.300 --> 18:24.065
appeal to the round table,

18:24.067 --> 18:26.132
or beg Clara Jackson
on bended knee

18:26.134 --> 18:27.732
for more of her powerball money,

18:27.734 --> 18:30.832
I do know that
it'll all run smoother...

18:30.834 --> 18:33.532
If we're a united front
under one roof.

18:37.667 --> 18:40.732
Well, my answer...

18:40.734 --> 18:42.631
Is no.

18:42.633 --> 18:43.932
Are you insane?

18:45.734 --> 18:49.065
There's a thin line between
keeping up appearances

18:49.067 --> 18:50.865
and flat-out hypocrisy.

18:53.933 --> 18:58.532
Now, you can go
and shuck and jive with Clara

18:58.534 --> 19:01.732
or whoever else will watch
and stop while you do it,

19:01.734 --> 19:03.599
but you do will do
it in the street...

19:05.200 --> 19:07.598
with the trash you seem to love.

19:07.600 --> 19:11.932
♪♪

19:11.934 --> 19:14.265
I'll come and get my things
in the morning.

19:14.267 --> 19:15.865
I don't care what you do.

19:15.867 --> 19:18.899
♪♪

19:25.967 --> 19:29.565
Tasha told me Britney
never talked to basie like that.

19:29.567 --> 19:30.932
She got to go.

19:30.934 --> 19:32.798
No, she's been there
since the church started,

19:32.800 --> 19:34.132
and she's good at her job.

19:34.134 --> 19:35.665
Yeah, but you didn't see the way

19:35.667 --> 19:37.865
she went in on <i> me</i>
and real church.

19:37.867 --> 19:40.065
Trust me, k,
you would've fired her.

19:42.667 --> 19:43.865
Hello?

19:43.867 --> 19:45.698
Jacob?

19:45.700 --> 19:47.032
I hope I'm not
bothering you, son.

19:47.034 --> 19:49.265
Nah, not bothering me
at all, pop.

19:49.267 --> 19:50.598
Tasha said she'd fire her.

19:50.600 --> 19:51.798
Oh, is Tasha first lady?

19:51.800 --> 19:53.332
No, that's not what I meant.

19:53.334 --> 19:54.465
What's up, pop?

19:54.467 --> 19:55.798
Listen, I just
wanted you to know

19:55.800 --> 20:00.532
that, uh, your mother
has thrown me out of the house.

20:00.534 --> 20:01.732
Thrown you out?

20:01.734 --> 20:03.665
I-it's not my idea.

20:03.667 --> 20:05.131
Oh, no, bishop?
Who?

20:06.034 --> 20:09.198
Uh, pop, uh,
hold on a second, okay?

20:09.200 --> 20:10.198
Just hold on.

20:10.200 --> 20:11.499
I'm gonna put you on hold.

20:13.000 --> 20:15.798
Hey, mama.
How you doin'?

20:15.800 --> 20:17.932
How's my granddaughter?

20:17.934 --> 20:20.198
She's fine.
How are you?

20:20.200 --> 20:23.165
Uh, pop told me you threw him
out of the house?

20:24.267 --> 20:25.532
Did he tell you why?

20:26.767 --> 20:29.165
No.
No, he didn't, did he?

20:29.167 --> 20:30.665
What's going on?

20:30.667 --> 20:32.665
I don't know.

20:32.667 --> 20:34.198
Um, but...

20:35.334 --> 20:38.332
I'm sorry, mama.
Just hold on real quick.

20:38.334 --> 20:39.398
Real quick.

20:41.034 --> 20:42.998
Hey, gigi.

20:43.000 --> 20:44.499
Jacob, we need to talk.

20:44.501 --> 20:48.132
Yeah, we do.

20:50.000 --> 20:52.332
♪♪

20:52.334 --> 20:53.998
You got to talk to mama.

20:54.000 --> 20:55.598
It's been one night.

20:55.600 --> 20:57.132
Going on two!

20:57.134 --> 20:59.332
She's never kicked him out
of the house before, has she?

20:59.334 --> 21:00.332
Or did I miss something?

21:00.334 --> 21:02.498
No, she hasn't, but...

21:02.500 --> 21:03.898
So this is different.

21:03.900 --> 21:05.532
Hey, what did daddy do?

21:05.534 --> 21:06.632
I don't know.

21:08.533 --> 21:10.398
I don't know!

21:10.400 --> 21:12.465
You know,
you're just not tellin' us.

21:12.467 --> 21:13.698
Yeah, I saw that look, too.

21:13.700 --> 21:15.699
Look, gigi,
just tell us what daddy did.

21:18.300 --> 21:20.499
He had an affair
with aunt mavis.

21:20.501 --> 21:22.565
That's not an affair,
that's before he married mama.

21:22.567 --> 21:23.865
Yeah, I mean,
even I know about that.

21:23.867 --> 21:26.198
No, no, no, no, this was
after they got married.

21:26.200 --> 21:27.265
More than once, y'all.

21:29.567 --> 21:32.265
They had an ongoing...?

21:33.633 --> 21:34.765
Yep.

21:38.767 --> 21:42.532
Gigi's right.
She's not gonna take him back.

21:42.534 --> 21:44.532
Who told you this?

21:44.534 --> 21:45.732
Mama did.

21:45.734 --> 21:47.332
And why did pop tell her?

21:47.334 --> 21:48.598
<i>He</i> didn't tell her,
<i>auntie</i> told her.

21:48.600 --> 21:49.965
They're gonna get a divorce.

21:49.967 --> 21:51.165
And from the way
he was talking today,

21:51.167 --> 21:52.565
it sounds like it's true.

21:52.567 --> 21:54.532
I'm gonna come
from a broken home.

21:54.534 --> 21:55.598
Really?
What are you, 12?

21:55.600 --> 21:57.465
Jacob, what are you, heartless?

21:57.467 --> 21:59.732
This is our parents
we're talking about.

21:59.734 --> 22:02.532
Our family, I mean come on.

22:02.534 --> 22:04.198
Gigi, you need to fix this.

22:04.200 --> 22:05.265
Why me?

22:05.267 --> 22:07.665
Why <i> you?</i>

22:07.667 --> 22:09.998
Gigi, before you came home,

22:10.000 --> 22:12.999
mama and aunt mavis
didn't even talk.

22:14.267 --> 22:18.532
Just... just talk to her,
okay, Jacob?

22:18.534 --> 22:21.231
Get her to forgive him,
take him back.

22:21.233 --> 22:23.099
Please.
I mean...

22:23.101 --> 22:25.232
Look, I'll check on mama
to check on mama,

22:25.234 --> 22:26.865
but all the grief
pop put me through

22:26.867 --> 22:28.331
after my little slip-up,

22:28.333 --> 22:31.265
he deserves a taste of what
he's so good at dishing out.

22:31.267 --> 22:32.398
This ain't about you.

22:32.400 --> 22:33.898
It ain't about you, either.

22:33.900 --> 22:34.900
What's your problem?

22:39.100 --> 22:40.698
What if my mother's right?

22:40.700 --> 22:42.598
She's not.

22:42.600 --> 22:43.865
You know she's not.

22:43.867 --> 22:45.198
Charity said none of this
would've happened

22:45.200 --> 22:47.299
if I didn't come home,
and I think she's right.

22:54.467 --> 22:56.165
They'll figure it out.

22:57.734 --> 22:59.865
Will you come to church
with me tomorrow?

22:59.867 --> 23:00.999
No.

23:03.000 --> 23:05.165
No?

23:05.167 --> 23:06.465
As a favor to me?

23:06.467 --> 23:08.965
And what good would that do?

23:08.967 --> 23:10.899
It would show
that you're in this with me.

23:10.901 --> 23:12.965
I am.

23:12.967 --> 23:14.898
That doesn't mean
I have to play my part

23:14.900 --> 23:18.232
in some soap opera
with a cross in the background.

23:18.234 --> 23:20.165
Wow.

23:20.167 --> 23:22.032
You know what I mean.

23:24.434 --> 23:26.365
Want to try me again
at Christmas?

23:26.367 --> 23:27.832
You know, don't joke about that.

23:27.834 --> 23:29.865
Well, don't ask me
to go to church.

23:32.667 --> 23:35.665
Okay, should I go before this
actually turns into a fight?

23:35.667 --> 23:36.798
It's not a fight.

23:36.800 --> 23:38.932
It's not.
It's not a fight.

23:38.934 --> 23:42.398
Yeah, 'cause i'MMA go home.

23:42.400 --> 23:43.865
No.
Yep.

23:43.867 --> 23:45.032
No.

23:50.134 --> 23:52.132
All right.

23:52.134 --> 23:53.865
I'm sorry.

23:53.867 --> 23:55.865
It's okay.
I'm just... I'm tired.

23:55.867 --> 23:57.132
That's all.
I know, it's good.

23:57.134 --> 23:59.398
I'll call you later.

23:59.400 --> 24:02.299
♪♪

24:40.167 --> 24:43.132
♪♪

24:58.467 --> 25:00.598
Mama?
Why aren't you dressed?

25:00.600 --> 25:02.165
First service starts
in half an hour.

25:03.867 --> 25:06.399
I-I can't go to church.

25:07.901 --> 25:09.798
The thought
of your father up there

25:09.800 --> 25:12.065
preaching like
everything is fine.

25:12.067 --> 25:14.465
How do you young people say it?

25:14.467 --> 25:15.965
I can't even.

25:17.467 --> 25:19.065
Well, what'll you do?

25:21.534 --> 25:22.699
I don't know.

25:24.000 --> 25:25.932
What do people do
on Sunday morning

25:25.934 --> 25:27.332
when they don't go to church?

25:28.334 --> 25:31.199
It's been so long,
I don't even remember.

25:50.334 --> 25:51.332
♪ Go knock ♪

25:51.334 --> 25:53.332
♪ pick a bushel full ♪

25:53.334 --> 25:56.265
♪ doors wide open,
waitin' for your soul ♪

25:56.267 --> 26:00.265
♪ I'm awake ♪

26:00.267 --> 26:03.532
♪ I have no need to fear ♪

26:03.534 --> 26:06.332
♪ 'cause he is ever near ♪

26:06.334 --> 26:08.865
♪ he'll know my work was true ♪

26:08.867 --> 26:11.532
♪ so glad the day is through ♪

26:11.534 --> 26:14.332
♪ it wasn't for me to say ♪

26:14.334 --> 26:17.065
♪ I didn't think
I'd make it today ♪

26:17.067 --> 26:18.832
♪ but I'm walkin',
not knockin' ♪

26:18.834 --> 26:20.298
♪ into heaven ♪

26:20.300 --> 26:22.098
♪ goodbye ♪

26:22.100 --> 26:25.298
♪ hey, you don't knock ♪

26:25.300 --> 26:27.731
♪ just walk right in ♪

26:27.733 --> 26:30.232
♪ all you got to do is walk ♪

26:30.234 --> 26:33.032
♪ walk right in ♪

26:33.034 --> 26:35.965
♪ walk right in ♪

26:35.967 --> 26:38.598
♪ just walk ♪

26:38.600 --> 26:41.098
♪ Jesus is waiting ♪

26:41.100 --> 26:43.665
♪ all you got to do is walk ♪

26:43.667 --> 26:46.165
♪ all you got to do is walk ♪

26:46.167 --> 26:49.331
♪ everything you need ♪

26:49.333 --> 26:52.131
Lady Mae is ill, I assume.

26:52.133 --> 26:54.465
You know, she's got a cold.

26:54.467 --> 26:56.065
I'll keep her in my prayers.

26:56.067 --> 26:57.865
God bless you, thank you.

26:57.867 --> 26:59.932
♪ He said ♪

26:59.934 --> 27:03.332
♪ hey ♪

27:03.334 --> 27:05.732
♪ the door ♪

27:05.734 --> 27:07.565
♪ there's love ♪

27:07.567 --> 27:11.032
♪ oh, love to share ♪

27:11.034 --> 27:13.831
♪ I know ♪

27:13.833 --> 27:16.499
♪ to rest ♪

27:16.501 --> 27:18.398
♪ you don't knock ♪

27:18.400 --> 27:21.932
♪ doors wide open,
waitin' for your soul ♪

27:21.934 --> 27:24.298
♪ don't knock ♪
♪ don't knock ♪

27:24.300 --> 27:31.265
♪ just walk on in ♪

27:31.267 --> 27:35.899
♪ hey ♪

27:35.901 --> 27:37.298
Hallelujah!

27:37.300 --> 27:39.765
Amen, amen.

27:39.767 --> 27:41.165
Oh, charity, baby.

27:46.300 --> 27:47.832
Thank you, charity.

27:47.834 --> 27:50.932
Now, I believe
she gave sister staples

27:50.934 --> 27:53.198
a run for her money, don't you?

27:56.267 --> 27:59.132
♪♪

28:44.134 --> 28:47.065
♪♪

28:58.800 --> 29:00.131
Before we get started,

29:00.133 --> 29:02.465
I want to call
a little attention today

29:02.467 --> 29:04.599
to my lovely granddaughter
Sophia,

29:04.601 --> 29:06.532
who is up here with me today.

29:09.267 --> 29:12.865
Lady Mae is dealing with some
family matters in little rock.

29:12.867 --> 29:16.065
Let us all pray for her,
for her safe return.

29:16.067 --> 29:17.432
All: Amen.
Amen.

29:19.667 --> 29:20.765
Now, today...

29:22.934 --> 29:27.065
i want to talk about...

29:27.067 --> 29:29.265
The the unimaginable courage...

29:30.600 --> 29:32.665
of Jesus of nazareth.

29:32.667 --> 29:33.999
Preach, bishop!

29:37.734 --> 29:39.832
Are you listening to me?

29:39.834 --> 29:44.665
Now, many of us face
hardships every day...

29:44.667 --> 29:47.999
Situations that we go into
not knowing

29:48.001 --> 29:50.798
what is going to be the outcome.

29:51.867 --> 29:54.799
♪♪

30:02.334 --> 30:04.099
♪♪

30:04.101 --> 30:08.298
Now, see we are all Shepherd...
Not just one,

30:08.300 --> 30:10.698
not two, not three,<i> all</i> of us!

30:13.400 --> 30:16.532
♪♪

30:16.534 --> 30:18.865
We're all his sheep
and we're all his Shepherds.

30:18.867 --> 30:21.665
We got to take care of
one another, protect each other,

30:21.667 --> 30:23.998
save our children from sin!

30:26.667 --> 30:28.799
Every single one of us!

30:28.801 --> 30:30.465
♪♪

30:30.467 --> 30:32.865
You see when that one sheep
slips out of our sight,

30:32.867 --> 30:34.198
don't we run after it?

30:35.334 --> 30:37.399
Don't matter
if it's one or a thousand,

30:37.401 --> 30:41.265
we do anything we can
to get it back,

30:41.267 --> 30:43.332
and oh, how we rejoice...

30:45.267 --> 30:47.665
when we hear that lonely bleat.

30:47.667 --> 30:48.667
Amen!

30:52.434 --> 30:54.132
What is lost?

30:54.134 --> 30:55.665
We're <i> all</i> lost!

30:57.367 --> 30:58.532
Lady Mae?

31:00.800 --> 31:03.565
How come you're not at calvary?

31:07.667 --> 31:09.332
Oh, would you like a cup of tea?

31:09.334 --> 31:11.465
Oh, I'd love one.

31:11.467 --> 31:12.532
Of course!

31:19.934 --> 31:22.065
Is this what
they have you doing?

31:22.067 --> 31:24.031
What do you mean?

31:24.033 --> 31:26.432
Well, you used to be first lady.

31:27.767 --> 31:31.865
Yeah, first lady.

31:31.867 --> 31:34.265
Um, would you hand me
those fudge stripes

31:34.267 --> 31:35.665
right there, please?

31:35.667 --> 31:36.865
The which?

31:36.867 --> 31:39.532
Those there, the fudge stripes.

31:50.800 --> 31:51.865
Have one!

31:51.867 --> 31:54.299
Oh, no, thank you.
Oh, I insist, please.

31:56.734 --> 31:59.599
These things always go so fast.

32:01.600 --> 32:05.598
So, I heard a story about
a first lady from Winston-Salem

32:05.600 --> 32:06.798
the other day.

32:08.067 --> 32:11.198
After 27 years of leading
a flock with her husband,

32:11.200 --> 32:14.198
he ended up leaving her
for a younger woman.

32:14.200 --> 32:15.732
She got tossed up
out of the church

32:15.734 --> 32:18.132
and ended up moving into
one of those apartment complexes

32:18.134 --> 32:19.798
you see
on the side of the highway,

32:19.800 --> 32:20.998
where the sign says,

32:21.000 --> 32:23.465
"if you lived here,
you'd be home by now."

32:25.600 --> 32:26.600
Here you go.

32:28.334 --> 32:30.831
Doesn't seem fair, does it?

32:30.833 --> 32:32.065
Oh, just wait.

32:32.067 --> 32:34.899
She ends up coming home from
the grocery store one night...

32:34.901 --> 32:36.031
Mm-hmm.

32:36.033 --> 32:37.898
Falls and trips
on the outside stairs.

32:37.900 --> 32:39.199
Oh, no.

32:39.201 --> 32:42.665
Tumbles over the balcony,
falls two stories,

32:42.667 --> 32:44.798
hits her head,
and now she can't even talk.

32:44.800 --> 32:48.465
Oh, my lord.
She lives in a home.

32:48.467 --> 32:51.265
One eye is like this.

32:51.267 --> 32:52.798
Like this.

32:52.800 --> 32:54.398
Like this!

32:54.400 --> 32:56.532
Look!
Look at the eye!

32:58.067 --> 33:00.098
I've got it good.

33:03.767 --> 33:05.965
Did... did I say
something wrong?

33:05.967 --> 33:09.165
The point I was making
is that I'm blessed.

33:09.167 --> 33:10.565
I mean, we both are.

33:10.567 --> 33:11.632
Yes, yes.

33:11.634 --> 33:13.598
I mean, even you more than me.

33:13.600 --> 33:16.465
At least you still
have a husband.

33:16.467 --> 33:17.665
♪♪

33:17.667 --> 33:18.732
Mine's gone.

33:18.734 --> 33:22.265
♪♪

33:22.267 --> 33:24.465
Thank you for the tea.

33:24.467 --> 33:26.798
Oh, well, you didn't want
to stay and say bye

33:26.800 --> 33:27.998
to kerissa and Jacob?

33:29.467 --> 33:31.532
I, uh, I think I should go.

33:31.534 --> 33:34.165
♪♪

33:44.667 --> 33:48.032
♪♪

33:57.800 --> 34:01.065
Let us bow our heads.

34:01.067 --> 34:03.631
Father god,

34:03.633 --> 34:08.031
we promise to use these gifts
to heal your people.

34:08.033 --> 34:11.797
Every dollar goes
straight to you!

34:11.800 --> 34:15.197
Bless these tithes
and offerings father,

34:15.199 --> 34:17.364
in Jesus' name...

34:17.367 --> 34:18.565
Amen.

34:18.567 --> 34:19.764
All: Amen.

34:19.766 --> 34:22.531
♪♪

34:22.533 --> 34:23.899
There you go.

34:25.867 --> 34:29.065
But it wasn't quite church.

34:29.067 --> 34:31.998
Oh, honey, you did a great job.

34:32.000 --> 34:34.732
I could barely
get through that sermon.

34:34.734 --> 34:37.264
The whole time I just
kept worrying about whether zora

34:37.266 --> 34:40.331
was gonna run out
the back doors of the church.

34:40.333 --> 34:42.998
There's a therapist
that specializes in
this kind of thing

34:43.000 --> 34:46.665
that I refer parents to when
the teachers report an issue.

34:46.667 --> 34:49.065
I can call her
first thing tomorrow morning.

34:49.067 --> 34:50.465
It's gonna take
more than counseling

34:50.467 --> 34:51.998
to get this girl's head
on right.

34:52.000 --> 34:53.532
It's gonna take an act of god.

34:53.534 --> 34:55.465
And whatever it takes,

34:55.467 --> 34:57.265
we're gonna get through it.

34:59.334 --> 35:00.465
Yes.

35:00.467 --> 35:02.932
Everything all right, pastor?

35:02.934 --> 35:04.865
Why do you ask?

35:04.867 --> 35:07.465
You just seemed
a little off your game today,

35:07.467 --> 35:08.732
and based on the offering,

35:08.734 --> 35:10.132
I'm not
the only one that noticed.

35:13.100 --> 35:14.965
Y-you hear this, right?

35:16.301 --> 35:18.232
Britney...
What?

35:18.234 --> 35:19.399
You're fired.

35:21.000 --> 35:22.865
Why?

35:22.867 --> 35:23.998
Why?

35:24.000 --> 35:25.998
Because we need people
who are interested

35:26.000 --> 35:27.598
in helping us achieve our goals.

35:27.600 --> 35:29.598
What?!

35:29.600 --> 35:33.265
Britney!
You're fired.

35:33.267 --> 35:34.465
Leave!

35:35.534 --> 35:36.965
Goodbye!

35:45.200 --> 35:47.265
I thought we were gonna talk.

35:47.267 --> 35:49.998
I told you what Tasha said.

35:50.000 --> 35:51.998
This is for the best.

35:52.000 --> 35:53.198
Trust me.

35:53.200 --> 35:56.199
♪♪

36:04.667 --> 36:06.132
Yeah.
Yeah?

36:06.134 --> 36:08.832
♪♪

36:11.734 --> 36:13.465
I'm gonna get back to you
about that, okay?

36:13.467 --> 36:15.332
Just give me two seconds.

36:15.334 --> 36:17.865
♪♪

36:17.867 --> 36:19.198
What are you doing here?

36:19.200 --> 36:20.299
You hung up on me.

36:20.301 --> 36:22.099
Yeah, you've got a lot of nerve.

36:22.101 --> 36:23.999
Well, it's Sunday morning,
charity.

36:24.001 --> 36:26.465
This is my church.
It's also my son's church.

36:26.467 --> 36:28.798
Oh, the son that you abandoned?

36:28.800 --> 36:31.932
Well, I'm back now,
and our agreement stipulates

36:31.934 --> 36:33.732
that I have a right
to see my son.

36:33.734 --> 36:35.265
Kevin, I can't believe you.

36:35.267 --> 36:36.865
So when can I see him?

36:36.867 --> 36:37.798
I don't know!

36:37.800 --> 36:40.132
I go back out
on tour tomorrow night,

36:40.134 --> 36:41.532
so I don't know.

36:41.534 --> 36:42.865
Well, leave him with me, then.

36:42.867 --> 36:45.532
Yeah, we'll see.

36:46.534 --> 36:48.532
It's not gonna be a we'll see.

36:48.534 --> 36:50.065
Excuse me?

36:50.067 --> 36:52.665
You either leave him with me
or you stay,

36:52.667 --> 36:55.699
but you're not taking my son
across state lines.

36:57.000 --> 36:58.798
That's kidnapping.

36:58.800 --> 37:01.799
♪♪

37:09.033 --> 37:10.031
♪♪

37:10.033 --> 37:12.498
Sister Greenland.

37:12.500 --> 37:13.898
Miss cross.

37:13.900 --> 37:15.565
You're still
director of outreach, right?

37:15.567 --> 37:17.032
Certainly am.

37:17.034 --> 37:20.865
Ah, well, if you ever need
one of your pet projects funded,

37:20.867 --> 37:23.932
I know how those deacons,
those old biddies can be.

37:23.934 --> 37:26.065
You let me know.

37:26.067 --> 37:27.332
I might take you up on that.

37:27.334 --> 37:30.065
Please do,
because finance is my thing.

37:30.067 --> 37:34.165
Oh, and thank god zora's home.

37:34.167 --> 37:36.265
God is good.

37:36.267 --> 37:37.732
All the time.

37:37.734 --> 37:40.665
♪♪

37:50.467 --> 37:54.198
Okay, so, do you want to wait
'til the morning

37:54.200 --> 37:56.065
to drive to Jackson?

37:56.067 --> 37:59.999
Or we'll leave tonight,
beat the traffic?

38:00.001 --> 38:02.532
I know a really romantic spot
on the way... Grenada lake.

38:02.534 --> 38:05.265
Wake up to the beach
outside the window.

38:05.267 --> 38:06.832
I can't go to Jackson

38:06.834 --> 38:11.198
or come back on the tour...
Or not yet.

38:11.200 --> 38:12.732
Seriously? Okay,
you can't just step out

38:12.734 --> 38:14.132
in the middle
of a tour like that, charity.

38:14.134 --> 38:16.998
Jabari, I don't want to,
but I have to.

38:17.000 --> 38:19.798
Kevin's back, and he's not
letting me take Nathan with me.

38:19.800 --> 38:21.765
But you signed a contract.

38:21.767 --> 38:26.065
This is my child
we're taking about.

38:26.067 --> 38:27.732
Look, Jabari,

38:27.734 --> 38:32.732
I just got to figure this out
with Kevin before I leave.

38:32.734 --> 38:34.332
Please.

38:38.267 --> 38:41.532
Britney, baby,
now, you know how they are.

38:41.534 --> 38:45.765
They've had it in for you ever
since they forced basie out.

38:47.467 --> 38:48.798
I know, I know.

38:48.800 --> 38:51.198
Well, look, it's just
time to move on now, okay?

38:51.200 --> 38:53.765
Give god the space
to do his thang!

38:56.067 --> 39:00.198
All right, well, you know
you can call me anytime.

39:00.200 --> 39:02.198
Okay?

39:02.200 --> 39:04.065
All right.

39:04.067 --> 39:06.065
Bye.

39:07.800 --> 39:09.732
That girl is so stupid.

39:11.400 --> 39:13.198
Okay, so what do you think
about this?

39:13.200 --> 39:14.798
Ooh, for the bishop?

39:14.800 --> 39:16.599
Mm-hmm.
Yes.

39:16.601 --> 39:18.665
Child, that man had me alone
in that hotel room

39:18.667 --> 39:20.665
and didn't do a thing.

39:20.667 --> 39:23.132
Well, I guess
I got to step my game up.

39:24.600 --> 39:26.865
Well,
that'll definitely kill 'em.

39:26.867 --> 39:28.465
What a tragedy.

39:34.867 --> 39:37.265
Oh, what about that one?

39:43.167 --> 39:47.132
Hey.
Sorry I'm late.

39:47.134 --> 39:48.832
How was church?

39:50.167 --> 39:51.765
It was strange.

39:51.767 --> 39:53.999
But thank you for asking.

39:55.434 --> 39:57.598
It's the least I could do.

39:57.600 --> 39:59.165
What happened?

40:00.934 --> 40:02.398
This Rochelle cross woman...

40:02.400 --> 40:04.598
She's gotten awfully close
with my father,

40:04.600 --> 40:06.799
and I feel like she's trying
to cozy up to me, too.

40:08.301 --> 40:10.799
What do you think she wants?

40:10.801 --> 40:12.131
I don't know,

40:12.133 --> 40:15.132
but I feel like she's trying to
come between my parents.

40:15.134 --> 40:18.065
I know she's done it
at another church.

40:18.067 --> 40:19.499
She's not gonna do it at mine.

40:19.501 --> 40:20.532
Yours?

40:21.501 --> 40:23.032
That's new.

40:24.667 --> 40:26.865
No matter what my mother thinks,

40:26.867 --> 40:31.365
no matter what she says,
this church matters to me.

40:33.400 --> 40:35.398
My family...

40:35.400 --> 40:36.865
Even more so.

40:40.800 --> 40:44.865
I won't let either of them
go down without a fight.

40:46.467 --> 40:49.465
♪♪

41:04.701 --> 41:07.065
I just came to get my things.

41:07.067 --> 41:10.065
♪♪

41:13.534 --> 41:15.198
James?

41:15.200 --> 41:18.099
♪♪

41:20.400 --> 41:21.565
Yes?

41:24.400 --> 41:26.465
You can come home,
but only until

41:26.467 --> 41:28.932
we figure out out this mess
with the I.R.S.

41:31.067 --> 41:33.431
And after that, I don't know.

41:33.433 --> 41:36.399
